@title{Testsuite Invokation}
@author{Jose F. Morales}

The @apl{ciaotool tests} command allows the invokation of the @em{test
suite} and check its results.

@section{Usage}

@tt{ciaotool tests ACTION}
  
@section{Available actions}

@item Compiler and full tests:

@begin{itemize}
@item @tt{full}: Full tests (comp + inccomp + (@tt{update-all}) + runexec + check)
@item @tt{comp}: Compiler check
@item @tt{inccomp}: Incremental compiler check
@end{itemize}

@item The following are only possible after performing @tt{update-all}:

@begin{itemize}
@item @tt{runexecs}: Test case execution (run the tests cases)
@item @tt{check}: Test case compilation (compare the compilation output)
@end{itemize}

@item Performance tests:

@begin{itemize}
@item @tt{eval}: Test case evaluation (performance and bytecode size)
@end{itemize}

@item Compare test output:

@begin{itemize}
@item @tt{briefcompare}: Show a summary of compilation results that differs
@item @tt{compare}: Compare saved results (invoking @app{meld} for each pair of files)
@item @tt{save}: Save results
@end{itemize}

@item Absmach generation actions:

@begin{itemize}
@item @tt{sabsmach-min}: Absmach machine minimization benchmarks
@item @tt{sabsmach-vers}: Absmach machine versions benchmarks
@end{itemize}



